review_text: This is yet another park on Boulevard Gouin that follows the Riviere-des-Prairies river. Being one of the longer ones, it offers a wider variety of panoramas, but the best ones remain those that you get on the river. I would have given it 5 stars had the riverfront been cleaner, but the municipality does precious little maintenance on its parks, especially those that do not attract large crowds.

(Translated by Google) Super nice place to go for a walk along the river from Montreal-North. No need to go far to relax in nature.

(Original)
Super bel endroit pour aller faire une marche le long de la rivière à partir de Montréal-Nord. Pas besoin d'aller loin pour se détendre dans la nature .

(Translated by Google) To do for a good little walk

(Original)
À faire pour une bonne petite marche
